THIRD-PARTY TOOLS — IMPORTANT

This Expansion ships NO third-party binaries. Its install scripts fetch the
following free, open-source tools at install time, from their official
sources, into your system package manager or this Expansion folder. Each is
licensed by its own authors under its own license; this myICOR license does
NOT cover them:

  - ffmpeg            (LGPL/GPL — https://ffmpeg.org)
  - whisper.cpp / ggml-org whisper builds (MIT — https://github.com/ggml-org/whisper.cpp)
  - whisper ggml model files (MIT — https://huggingface.co/ggerganov/whisper.cpp)
  - yt-dlp            (Unlicense — https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp)
  - pandoc            (GPL-2.0-or-later — https://pandoc.org)
  - ImageMagick       (ImageMagick License — https://imagemagick.org)
  - qpdf              (Apache-2.0 — https://qpdf.sourceforge.io)
  - poppler / poppler-utils (GPL-2.0 — https://poppler.freedesktop.org)
  - trafilatura       (Apache-2.0 — https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura)
  - libheif           (LGPL — https://github.com/strukturag/libheif)
  - ExifTool          (Perl Artistic / GPL-1.0-or-later — https://exiftool.org)
  - OCRmyPDF          (MPL-2.0 — https://github.com/ocrmypdf/OCRmyPDF)
  - Tesseract OCR     (Apache-2.0 — https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract)
  - Ghostscript       (AGPL-3.0 — https://www.ghostscript.com)

AGPL COMPONENT NOTICE — Ghostscript

As of v1.1.0 this pack's optional OCR feature (making a scanned PDF
searchable) uses OCRmyPDF, which relies on Ghostscript. Ghostscript is
licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0).

The pack ships NO Ghostscript binary and NO Ghostscript source. Ghostscript
is fetched at install time from your system package manager, and it is used
ONLY as a separate local command-line process that OCRmyPDF spawns on your
own machine. This pack does not modify Ghostscript, does not link or embed
its code, and does not expose it over any network. Used this way, the AGPL
copyleft applies to Ghostscript itself (your package manager provides its
source and license) and does not extend to this pack or to your files.
If you do not use the OCR feature, Ghostscript is never invoked.

